<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id778bd432-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s426a"><num value="426a">§ 426a.</num><heading> Qualifications of members of commission</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In appointing the members of the commission created by <ref href="/us/usc/t16/s426">section 426 of this title</ref> the Secretary of the Interior shall, as far as practicable, select persons familiar with the terrain of the battlefield of Stones River, Tennessee, and the historical events associated therewith.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id778bd433-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/act/1927-03-03/ch374/s2">Mar. 3, 1927, ch. 374, § 2</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/44/1399">44 Stat. 1399</ref>; Ex. Ord. No. 6166, § 2, <date date="1933-06-10">June 10, 1933</date>; Ex. Ord. No. 6228, § 1, <date date="1933-07-28">July 28, 1933</date>.)</sourceCredit>
